{
  "texts": [
    "Results Tool use and retrieval improve LLM responsesTo first demonstrate the superiority of combining medical tools and retrieval with an LLM, we compared our agent to GPT-4 alone.",
    "As an illustration, in Fig. 2a, we highlight three examples where tools and retrieval enabled the LLM to accurately solve cases, whereas, without these enhancements, GPT-4 either stated that it could not solve the patient case and provided hypothetical answers instead or drew incorrect conclusions, such as falsely assuming 'disease progression' or 'no evidence of disease' (in red).",
    "In contrast, the agent, by using tools, correctly identified treatment response and the presence of disease progression (in green).",
    "To quantify this, we assessed the model's ability to develop a comprehensive treatment plan for each patient, specifying appropriate therapies on the basis of recognizing disease progression, response or stability, mutational profile and all other relevant information, much like an oncologist would.",
    "Therefore, we compiled a set of 109 statements (completeness) for 20 different patient cases."
  ]
}